events.body:
> The memory difference is measurable and non-negligible (~200MiB, seems the buffer may be copied 4 times), especially for small memory usecases.
> I have opened [google/leveldb#1259](https://github.com/google/leveldb/pull/1259) to enable pre-sizing the memory, which might help us in reducing the spikes slightly.

@l0rinc  you can also check `leveldb.approximate-memory-usage`. [Use db.GetProperty](https://github.com/google/leveldb/blob/main/include/leveldb/db.h#L122) before and after batch writes. I noticed that it shows a non-negligible spike in memory usage. Could be useful to quickly check if https://github.com/google/leveldb/pull/1259 works

